Good question!
I believe what happens is this; when the server lags, the game tries to ‘catch up’ by firing multiple ticks in quick succession. Sometimes from bigger lag, the server might even try to fire multiple ticks at the exact same time. This causes issues with redstone when it tries to skip ahead and predict what redstone component should be activated next, so when it tries to activate an entire circuit in ‘one tick’ (which is really just a bunch of ticks fired at the same time, to catch up with the server lag) somethings like pistons or repeaters won’t update properly, causing desyncs.

Take this with a grain of salt, I’m not an expert and this could be completely wrong, but it’s what I believe is happening
